{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}} {{Use British English|date=April 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Harry Adamson | image = | fullname = | birth_date = c. 1913 <!-- See talk page --> | birth_place = [[Scunthorpe]], England | death_date = | height = | position = [[Striker (association football)|Centre forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Upton Colliery F.C.|Upton Colliery]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 1933–1937 | clubs2 = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] | caps2 = 29 | goals2 = 19 | years3 = 1937–1938 | clubs3 = [[Aldershot F.C.|Aldershot]] | caps3 = 4 | goals3 = 1 }} '''Harry Adamson''' (c. 1913 – after 1937) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who played at [[Striker (association football)|centre forward]]. He was born in [[Scunthorpe]].
Adamson was playing for [[Upton Colliery F.C.|Upton Colliery]] when he signed for [[Football League]] club [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] in October 1933. He played just 29 league games for the club in three years but scored 19 goals,<ref>{{cite book|title=Football League players' records 1888 to 1939|author=Michael Joyce|publisher=SoccerData|isbn=1-899468-67-6}}</ref> including ten from only 12 games in [[1934-35 in English football|1934–35]] to be the club's leading goal-scorer. He left for [[Aldershot F.C.|Aldershot]] in May 1937.
