{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Liphistius batuensis'' | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | classis = [[Arachnid]]a | ordo = [[Spider|Araneae]] | subordo = [[Mesothelae]] | familia = [[Liphistiidae]] | genus = ''[[Liphistius]]'' | species = '''''L. batuensis''''' | binomial = ''Liphistius batuensis'' | binomial_authority = Abraham, 1923 }}
'''''Liphistius batuensis''''' is a species of [[trapdoor spider (disambiguation)|trapdoor spider]] from [[Malaysia]]. It is thought to be restricted to the [[Batu Caves]], near [[Kuala Lumpur]].<ref>{{cite journal|author=Liz Price |year=2004 |title=An introduction to some cave fauna of Malaysia and Thailand |journal=[[Acta Carsologica]] |volume=33 |issue=1 |pages=311–317 |url=http://carsologica.zrc-sazu.si/downloads/331/liz.pdf |format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110726183049/http://carsologica.zrc-sazu.si/downloads/331/liz.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-26 |df= }}</ref> It was first collected by H. C. Abraham in 1923, and has been described as a [[living fossil]].<ref name="mcclure">{{cite journal |author=H. Elliott McClure, Boo-Liat Lim & Sarah E. Winn |year=1967 |title=Fauna of the Dark Cave, Batu Caves, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia |journal=[[Pacific Insects]] |volume=9 |issue=3 |pages=399–428 |url=http://hbs.bishopmuseum.org/pi/pdf/9(3)-399.pdf |format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]}}</ref>
Adults build a nest which is {{convert|40|-|50|mm}} long with an opening some {{convert|22|mm|1}} wide, from which six to ten strands of [[spider silk|silk]] radiate out {{convert|12.5|-|15|cm|0}} in a semicircle. The movement of an insect against these threads is detected by the spider which then rushes out and captures the insect.<ref name="mcclure"/> Spiderlings build smaller nests, only {{convert|10|mm|1}} across, and seem to abandon these during development to build a bigger nest; intermediate sizes of nest are not seen.<ref name="mcclure"/>
Spiders of all ages may fall prey to cave-dwelling [[centipede]]s.<ref name="mcclure"/>
