'''Marwysgafn''' is a [[Welsh language|Welsh]] term meaning a "deathbed song". Used by poets when they sense they are close to death, the poet confesses and asks for forgiveness. Marwysgafns were primarily popular during the [[Medieval Welsh literature#Poets of the Princes (ca. 1100 – ca. 1300)|Poets of the Princes]] period. <ref name="ref1">{{cite web|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/367251/marwysgafn|title=Encyclopædia Britannica online entry for Marwysgafn|accessdate=2012-05-29}}</ref>
